---
/**
 * Station 5: Building New Things
 * Primary concept: Creating new DOM elements from scratch and adding/removing them
 * Code role: Reinforcement (builds on all prior skills)
 * Characters: HAP only
 */
import StationLayout from '../../layouts/StationLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';

const introContent = `
    <p><strong>By Station 4, I had a full toolkit for working with elements that already existed on the page.</strong> I could find them, read them, change their text, toggle their classes, update their attributes. But every element I'd touched was one that was already in my HTML file &mdash; already part of the blueprint.</p>
    <p class="mt-1">Then I had an idea: what if I could add skill badges to my Robot ID Card? The card didn't have any badges in the HTML. There was no badge element to find.</p>
    <p class="mt-1">I'd need to create something from nothing. &#x1F7E0;</p>
`;
---
<!--
